ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Lagos, Nigeria’s economic powerhouse and epicentre of the Coronavirus pandemic on Friday reported an all-time high record of 254 new COVID-19 infections. This is the highest daily report, so far, of new confirmed cases since the index case in February in Lagos. The Lagos report is part of the 387 new cases confirmed and released late on Friday by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov.With  the latest report Nigeria’s total confirmed COVID-19 cases now total 9,302. The full report is as follows: Lagos-254FCT-29Jigawa-24Edo-22Oyo-15Rivers-14Kaduna-11Borno-6Kano-3Plateau-2Yobe-2Gombe-2Bauchi-2Ondo-1 9302 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 2697Deaths: 261 https://t.co/Pmmurht8H8 ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Lagos, Nigeria’s economic powerhouse and epicentre of the Coronavirus pandemic on Saturday reported an all-time high record of 378 new COVID-19 infections. This is the highest daily report, so far, of new confirmed cases since the index case in February in Lagos. 52 in the FCT, 23… May 31, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories" The Lagos State Government has announced that a 36-year-old man died of coronavirus in the state. The Lagos Commissioner for Health, Prof. Akin Abayomi, made the announcement via his Twitter handle on Sunday. He said that the Nigerian died on Saturday in a private facility. Abayomi confirmed the death as… April 5, 2020 In "News"